release.name: 2.0 Update
release.body:
This update adds ability scores, a new menu system, many new species traits, and more.

## New Features
### Menu System
- Accessed via `/function dnd:menu`
- Has 4 pages: Species, Cheats, Links, and Admin.
- Species page
  - Shows a list of all available species
  - Traits are shown in hover text
  - Some species (like elves and dwarves) have subpages for their subspecies.
  - Clicking on a species activates it.
    - This unfortunately gives a popup warning about the command, but you can ignore that.
- Cheats page
  - Shows 2 buttons for each cheat: Enable and Disable
- Links page
  - Shows various links to stuff about the pack
- Admin page
  - Only available to players with the `developer` tag.
  - Has several useful utilities which make debugging easier.
  - If you're planning on modifying this pack, or just want the neat utilities, run `/tag @s developer`, and it'll show up on the menu.
### Ability Scores
- There are 6 scores: Strength (STR), Dexterity (DEX), Constitution (CON), Intelligence (INT), Wisdom (WIS), and Charisma (CHA).
- Each score boosts certain traits.
  - STR boosts attack damage and attack knockback.
  - DEX boosts speed and agility.
  - CON boosts health and resistance to damage.
  - INT, WIS, and CHA currently don't boost anything, and this is due to a couple reasons.
    - Not really anything to boost. There aren't really any mental traits in Minecraft.
    - The few things I thought of would be very difficult to implement.
    - I plan to give these three scores uses in future updates, but for now they're useless.
- None of the boosts are insane, but they're minor little tweaks that you'll notice here and there.
- Each species gives a bonus to an ability score.
### New Species Traits
- Many new bonuses across nearly every species.
- Hill Dwarf
  - Extra heart
- Wood Elf
  - Turns invisible while sneaking in 2-block tall plants (tall grass, rose bush, sugarcane, etc).
- Aarakocra
  - Higher damage (Claws)
- Earth Genasi
  - Higher movement efficiency (like in soul sand)
- Goliath
  - Natural armor
- Bugbear
  - Longer attack/entity interact reach
- Shifter
  - Night vision
- Centaur
  - Higher damage (Hooves)
- Minotaur
  - Much higher damage (Horns)
- Satyr
  - Extra damage (Horns)
- Tortle
  - Extra damage (Claws)
    - Wait tortoises have claws???
  - Much longer breath
- Lizardfolk
  - Higher damage (Bite)
  - Natural armor (Only while not wearing armor)
- Aasimar
  - Healing Hands (Ability)
    - Heals nearby entity
    - Can be used once per day
- Firbolg
  - Temporary Invisibility
    - Turns you invisible for 10 seconds
    - Can be used once per day
- Eladrin
  - Can teleport like Shadar-Kai
- Kobold
  - Now gets periodic darkness effect like Dark Elves.
- Tabaxi
  - Higher damage (Claws)
  - Short speed boosts
    - Lasts for 10 seconds, recharges after 30 seconds
- Orc
  - Long speed boosts
    - Lasts for 60 seconds, can be used once a day
### Abilities Menu
- Access by pressing G (by default, differs if you've changed your quick options keybind)
- Lists all abilities
  - Not all are allowed to be used by your current species, but I am *not* going to create 300+ (once I add more abilities with like classes and stuff) just to display all the abilities your species can personally use.

### Wildhunt Shifter
- Has two different effects while shifted, depending on if other players are online.
- If in singleplayer, all nearby mobs have the glowing effect.
- If in multiplayer, all nearby mobs have a particle effect only visible to currently shifted Wildshape Shifters.
### Human
- Nothing interesting about them
## Changes
- Gnomes have been split into Forest and Rock Gnomes
  - This is so the new ability scores can differ across them.
- Githyanki and Githzerai are now under a Gith main species
  - This is so an ability score can match between them
    - Note: Githzerai suck, use Githyanki
- Eladrin are now properly in the elf species
  - Somehow I missed that.
- Teleporting is now an ability
  - You can activate the ability to get the ender pearl
  - It'll disappear after 10 seconds
  - If another player holds it, it'll also disappear.
    - This is one of a few anti-exploiting measures I've added when it comes to the teleporting ability.
- Messages put into chat (like "Unshifting...") now use `tellraw` instead of `say`
  - This prevents it from being visible to all players.
- Moved old menu system to `/function dnd:system/classic_menu`
  - This won't be updated much in the future, but I'm leaving it in the pack because I spent too much time on it to just delete it.
- Cheats are no longer reset upon world load/pack reload.
  - There are also separate commands for disabling/enabling cheats.
- Weapon proficiencies now increase attack speed instead of attack damage.
  - This just makes more sense.
- There are generally a few more messages that'll be put into chat to make debugging easier, and give more feedback for the user.

## Technical Changes
### Popup Title
- Popup title has been delayed a tiny bit, which hopefully should make it always appear to players without a species.
- The command for the popup title is now `/function dnd:system/popuptitle`, which is more accurate.
### Speed changes to counteract MC-195830
- Higher Speed is now set using a modifier, as modifiers aren't reset on world load.
- Lower speed is now set using a tagging system, so species with a lower speed will always have their speed set after world load, even if it's reset.
### Performance Optimizations
- Several reused targeters in the tick file have been moved to subfiles to reduce [forking](https://datapack.wiki/wiki/command/execute#forking).
- It's nothing major, but should significantly boost performance in big servers.
### Misc Technical Changes
- Added new crouch detection system.

## Bug Fixes
- Fixed speed being reset on world load.
  - This isn't a bug with my datapack, and it's actually a bug with Minecraft (MC-195830), but I still wanted to fix it, so I found a way to counteract it.

pull_request.title: feat: dynamic parameters, output structure, logging flags
pull_request.body:
## What changed (backend)

* Removed legacy form fields (quality, max_features, enable_gpu) from POST /upload.
* Added GET /parameters that loads/validates src/backend/fake_backend/parameters.json at startup (with safe defaults if missing).
* POST /upload now only accepts files and an optional parameters JSON string; if absent, defaults from parameters.json are used.
* Stored per-job parameters at output/backend/fake_backend/{job_id}/parameters.json; models saved under models/, uploads under uploads/.
* Added --log-level to server CLI; result_file_path recorded on model generation.

## What changed (frontends)

### Web v0.2:
* apiClient.js: added getParameters(); startProcessing now always sends parameters as a JSON field in FormData.
* parameterPanel.js: can load dynamic definitions from GET /parameters and render matching UI controls.
* app.js: fetches /parameters on init and feeds panel defaults; sends selected values on upload.

### CLI client:
* Added --verbose logging option; removed emojis; logging only.
* Can include dynamic parameters payload (server ignores legacy fields anyway).

## Quality and commit
* .gitignore updated to ignore output/ and generated artifacts.
* CHANGELOG updated (dynamic parameters, output structure, logging flags).
* Quick integration tests passed (backend startup, client flow, ws, download).

## Impact
* Clients must include a parameters JSON field with uploads or rely on server defaults from parameters.json.
* Web UI now reflects whatever is defined in parameters.json without code changes.

review.body:
## Greptile Summary

This PR adds support for boolean data types in the `list.max()` and `list.min()` functions, addressing issue #4914. Previously, these functions only accepted numeric types and would throw a TypeError when applied to lists of boolean values.

The changes involve updating type validation logic in two core Rust files:
- `src/daft-functions-list/src/max.rs`: Modified the `get_return_field()` function to accept boolean types alongside numeric types
- `src/daft-functions-list/src/min.rs`: Applied the same type validation update for consistency

The implementation leverages existing aggregation infrastructure that already supports boolean comparisons (where False < True in natural ordering). The change only required updating the schema validation from `field.dtype.is_numeric()` to `field.dtype.is_numeric() || field.dtype.is_boolean()` in both functions.

Comprehensive test coverage was added in `tests/recordbatch/list/test_list_bool_aggs.py`, verifying correct behavior across various scenarios including all-True/all-False lists, mixed boolean values, null handling, and both variable-length and fixed-size list types. The tests confirm that boolean semantics are properly implemented (True > False) and that null handling follows standard SQL conventions.

This enhancement provides consistency with other boolean aggregation functions already available in the codebase (like `list_bool_and` and `list_bool_or`) and aligns with user expectations for min/max operations on boolean data.

## Confidence score: 5/5

- This PR is safe to merge with minimal risk as it only extends existing functionality without breaking changes
- Score reflects straightforward type validation changes with comprehensive test coverage and consistent implementation patterns
- No files require special attention as the changes are well-contained and thoroughly tested

pull_request.title: chore(deps): bump react-pdf from 9.2.1 to 10.1.0
pull_request.body:
Bumps [react-pdf](https://github.com/wojtekmaj/react-pdf/tree/HEAD/packages/react-pdf) from 9.2.1 to 10.1.0.
Release notes

Sourced from react-pdf's releases.

v10.1.0

What's new?

  • Added support for functions as children. React-PDF has never been simpler to work with! Say goodbye toonLoadSuccess, say goodbye to setting number of pages in your own state, say goodbye to extra renders! Now, rendering a simple document is as trivial as: 
    <Document file="sample.pdf">
  {({ pdf }) => Array(pdf.numPages)
    .fill(null)
    .map((_, index) => <Page key={index} pageIndex={index} />
  ))}
</Document>
    Thanks @‚Äãadamaoc for inspiration!
  • Updated PDF.js to 5.3.93.
  • Updated documentation on JPEG 2000 support.
  • Updated dependencies.
  • Exported LinkService type for convenience.

What's changed?

  • usePageContext will now provide non-null value sooner than before, before the page is actually loaded. This is uniform with how useDocumentContext behaves and with how types were designed from the start, so you should not be affected by this change.
  • React-PDF now targets es2018 and not es2017. PDF.js, our core dependency, already used modern JavaScript syntax, so you should not be affected by this change.

v10.0.1

Bug fixes

  • Fixed commonly used types not reexported.

v10.0.0

See Upgrade guide from version 9.x to 10.x.

After more than a year since our last major release, we're thrilled to bring you React-PDF 10.

This update includes a major PDF.js upgrade, new features to make your life easier, improved stability, and some important breaking changes.

üëÄ Want to see exciting features more often? Consider sponsoring React-PDF.

‚ùóÔ∏è = breaking change

What's new?

  • ‚ùóÔ∏è Dropped CommonJS build, making the package ESM-only. Chances are you're not going to be affected by this change at all, as all common bundlers support ESM out of the box.
    • However, you may encounter issues running unit tests using Jest. Consider migrating to Vitest.
  • Updated PDF.js to 5.3.31.
    • Performance boosts: Key rendering routines refactored to cut memory usage and speed up page loading.
    • JPEG2000 downscaling: Automatic downscale of large JPEG2000 images during decoding to improve render times.
    • CMYK JPEG fix: Correct handling of the alpha channel when WebAssembly is disabled.
    • Viewer stability: Better handling of missing/invalid Content-Range headers.
    • API cleanup: Removed deprecated options, adopted parameter objects for core methods, and introduced private class fields for cleaner code.
  • Added support for scale prop in Document component, allowing you to set the scale for the entire document.

... (truncated)

issue.title: No search results
issue.body:
Is there any logs for this plugin? No matter how I search, the search results page is empty. And I saw this in my Jellyfin log:

```
[2025-08-15 22:05:03.137 +08:00] [ERR] Provider "Apple Music" failed to retrieve search results
System.ArgumentNullException: Value cannot be null. (Parameter 'stringToEscape')
   at System.ArgumentNullException.Throw(String paramName)
   at System.ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull(Object argument, String paramName)
   at System.UriHelper.EscapeString(String stringToEscape, Boolean checkExistingEscaped, SearchValues`1 noEscape)
   at Jellyfin.Plugin.ITunes.MetadataServices.AppleMusicMetadataService.Search(String searchTerm, ItemType type, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
   at Jellyfin.Plugin.ITunes.Providers.ITunesArtistMetadataProvider.GetUrlsForScraping(ArtistInfo info, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
   at Jellyfin.Plugin.ITunes.Providers.ITunesArtistMetadataProvider.GetSearchResults(ArtistInfo searchInfo, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
   at MediaBrowser.Providers.Manager.ProviderManager.GetRemoteSearchResults[TItemType,TLookupType](RemoteSearchQuery`1 searchInfo, BaseItem referenceItem, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
```

comment.body:
Hm, this is strange. Lookup either by name or by ID works for me just fine. With name lookup, I get 11 results. In case of lookup using ID, you should see this in the log (with enabled debug logging):
```
[16:14:32] [INF] [22] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.Providers.ArtistMetadataProvider   : Using ID 1576219850 for artist lookup
[16:14:32] [DBG] [22] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.Providers.ArtistMetadataProvider   : Getting artist by ID 1576219850
[16:14:32] [DBG] [22] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.MetadataSources.Web.WebMetadataSource   : Fetching artist from https://music.apple.com/us/artist/1576219850
[16:14:32] [DBG] [22] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.MetadataSources.Web.WebMetadataSource   : Opening page: https://music.apple.com/us/artist/1576219850
[16:14:33] [DBG] [20] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.MetadataSources.Web.WebMetadataSource   : Scraping artist from https://music.apple.com/us/artist/irys/1576219850
[16:14:33] [DBG] [20] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.MetadataSources.Web.Scrapers.ArtistScraper   : Artist scraping completed
[16:14:33] [DBG] [20] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.Providers.ArtistMetadataProvider   : Found artist by ID 1576219850
[16:14:33] [INF] [20] Jellyfin.Plugin.AppleMusic.Providers.ArtistMetadataProvider   : Found 1 results for ID 1576219850
```

The message about empty name is a bit misleading in case of using ID for identification, because the plugin still tried to use search to get more results. I removed that behavior in `.8` build, as it did not make much sense.

issue.title: RP2350/PICO2  assembler MOV error
issue.body:
### Port, board and/or hardware

RP2350/PICO2  

### MicroPython version

3.4.0; MicroPython v1.26.0 on 2025-08-09


### Reproduction

```py
#!/micropython
# -*- coding: UTF-8 -*-
# vim: fileencoding=utf-8: ts=4: sw=4: expandtab:

from sys import version

@micropython.asm_thumb
def test():
    mov     (r10,r0)

print(version)
print(test())
#       3.4.0; MicroPython v1.26.0 on 2025-08-09
#       Traceback (most recent call last):
#         File "<stdin>", line 12, in <module>
#       TypeError: 'int' object isn't callable
```


### Expected behaviour

Should works with all target registers R0‚Ä¶R12

### Observed behaviour

Works with target registers R0‚Ä¶R9,R11‚Ä¶R12
Does NOT work with R10

### Additional Information

No, I've provided everything above.

### Code of Conduct

Yes, I agree

comment.body: Registers R4 and onwards should be restored on exit - your function corrupts a register that holds other data needed by the interpreter...
